post_text:
Stanton I.S.D. is now using RankOne for all athletic medical paperwork. There is a link on the athletics page of the school website that gives you instructions on how to get to the RankOne website and fill out the paperwork. This is the UIL packet and Medical History that all athletes have to fill out every year and is required before participation in any athletic event is allowed.

Go to the following webpage and click on "Rank One Medical Paperwork Instructions":

https://www.stanton.esc18.net/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=1566260&type=d&pREC_ID=1696525

If you have any questions, contact Coach Hogan at chogan@stanton.esc18.net

Sigma Phi Epsilon is proud to offer the Balanced Man Scholarship at over 140 universities to student leaders this year with no obligation to join SigEp to be eligible.! This is a great opportunity for students entering college in fall 2020.

This resource is intended to assist with college affordability, while introducing students to campus life opportunities.

The scholarship application only takes 15 minutes, and early application deadlines are June 1, 2020, for several universities.

Click the link below to get started:

https://sigep.org/scholarships/

post_text:
Senior Parents and Students,

Last week, the Governor closed all schools for the remainder of the year. There are so many questions surrounding graduation and honoring our seniors.

•We are waiting for direction from the commissioner of education and what we can and cannot do.

•At this time we are still waiting to make a decision about graduation the first week of May.

•If you ordered from Herff-Jones, they will provide an insert for announcements once that decision is made.

•Due to the current uncertainties, I encourage you to communicate in your invitations: "Due to current circumstances, graduation information is tentative."

I know there are a lot of questions but we hope things begin to return to some semblance of normalcy. We don't want to make a decision now in hopes that the governor and commissioner of education loosen the current constraints.

Know that plans are in the works and we will communicate them ASAP.

Last week, the Governor closed all schools for the remainder of the year. There are so many questions surrounding graduation and honoring our seniors.

•If you ordered from Herff-Jones, they will provide an insert for announcements once that decision is made.

•Due to the current uncertainties, I encourage you to communicate in your invitations: "Due to current circumstances, graduation information is tentative."

I know there are a lot of questions but we hope things begin to return to some semblance of normalcy. We don't want to make a decision now in hopes that the governor and commissioner of education loosen the current constraints.

Know that plans are in the works and we will communicate them ASAP.

March 15 at 5:20 PM ·

As concerns grow regarding the spread of the Coronavirus (COVID-19) and it’s impact on the ongoing need to continue operations on providing food assistance to our community we will be doing a “no contact” distribution.
We ask that you drive up & we will take the food to your car. If we don’t see you for some reason please call or honk to let us know you are outside. On Wednesday we will be receiving our Senior boxes. So we will only be serving our senior citizens that day! For any questions please call the office at 756-3254!
We are trying to make this as smooth as we can please be patient with us.
We will be open an extra day next week. Schedule is as follows:
Monday:8-12 &1-3
Tuesday: 8-12 & 1-3
Wednesday:12:30-3 SENIORS ONLY
Thursday: 8-12 & 1-3

post_text: At approximately 10:45 am, Stanton High School received a report of a possible firearm on campus. Stanton High school was placed on a precautionary lockdown to provide law enforcement the opportunity to investigate the report. As an additional precaution, Stanton Elementary and Middle School were sheltered in place. Once law enforcement determined there was not a threat to the school, the lockdown was lifted. Students have returned to their normal schedule. Stanton I.S.D. takes all threats seriously and will take the necessary precautions to ensure the protection of our students and staff.

Juniors and Seniors!!!!!

We are offering the ACT test without writing during the school day on October 1st. The cost of the test is $45.50.

If you are interested in taking the ACT on October 1st, please email me at mhenson@stanton.esc18.net TODAY, August 29th. You will need to pay your $45.50 by next Friday, September 6th to ensure your spot. Checks can be made out to Stanton High School.

There will be another chance to take the ACT here at the high school in February. If you choose to wait, we are setting up criteria that you can work on during advisement to earn free ACT testing during the February administration. More to come in the near future!

Feel free to take advantage of both testing days!

ATTENTION STUDENTS: If you are interested in being in Student Council, we have already hit the floor running to get ready for a MARVELous year. There are several opportunities for you to serve before school starts and earn community service hours and points to help secure your spot to attend the State Convention in April. We have a lot of exciting things planned for this year, and I promise...you want to be a part of the action. If you are interested, please contact Mrs. Garrett (agarrett@stanton.esc18.net) to find out how you can get started.
Also, be sure to follow us on Instagram to be one of the first to know what all we have going on. Who knows...you may see yourself featured throughout the year!
Side note: if you are an NHS member and are looking for ways to get your community service hours, we would love to have your help as well.

It’s never too early (or too late) to be looking for scholarships. That’s why we’re working with Going Merry to make finding and applying to scholarships simple. They have thousands of scholarships on their site and we've created a Stanton High School page, where you can see your local and national scholarships (many of which have no essays and take less than 30 minutes to compete), all in one place. It’s easy to use and absolutely free!

View your scholarships on our school page at:

https://www.goingmerry.com/edu/stanton-high-school-stanton-tx

Good luck with your scholarship applications!

– Mrs. Henson

As we approach the dreaded flu season-- please read through this information provided by the CDC.

If your student has a fever, please keep them home. Call the office and let us know they're sick so their absence can be excused. If your student is sick more than 3 days, a doctor's note is required to excuse the 4th absence. REMEMBER STUDENTS MUST BE FEVER FREE FOR 24 HOURS (WITHOUT MEDICATION) BEFORE RETURNING TO SCHOOL.

Juniors and Seniors:

We would like to offer the SAT on March 27th here at the high school. If you are interested in taking the SAT during school hours, please sign up in the office by next Friday, January 18th. The test cost $64.50 with essay or $47.50 without the essay. If you qualify for free or reduced lunches, come see me for the reduced amount. This is a great opportunity to take the SAT here at the high school instead of using a Saturday and having to go somewhere else.

For more information, visit:

satschoolday.org/success

Cradle
Small Desk and chair
Old suitcase
Old trunk
Wooden table with six chairs (one a captains chair with arms, optional)
Two straight back chairs
Desk and chair
Table high enough for someone to sit at.
Sideboard
Dishware and utensils for a meal – preferably unbreakable
Drink glasses
Small sturdy bed for a child
Sewing basket
Dr. bag black leather type
Water pitcher
Basin and pitcher
If you have any items that you can donate please contact Mrs. Harp. aharp@Stanton.esc18.net

post_text:
Just a reminder:

You need to create FSA Id’s TODAY!!!!

SENIOR PARENTS:

FAFSA NIGHT
Tuesday, October 16th at 5:30 in Room 108

*** There will be representatives here from Panhandle Plains and Howard College to assist you with your college FAFSA paperwork.

You and your child will need to create a FSA ID before you come to the meeting. Instructions on how to do this have been emailed to your student's school email - be sure to ask them about it!

You will also need your 2017 tax return information.

Please be sure to check out the reference materials I attached in your child's school email - they will be very helpful when creating your FSA ID and completing your FAFSA.

Feel free to email me for your own email with the attached information at mhenson@stanton.esc18.net

Here is the link to create your FSA ID.
https://fsaid.ed.gov/npas/index.htm
